    <summaries>
      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <actionDate>2016-03-03</actionDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Strengthening the Department of Homeland Security Secure Mail Initiative Act</strong></p> <p>This bill requires the Department of Homeland Security to provide an option under the Secure Mail Initiative under which, for payment of a fee recouping costs, a person to whom a document is sent under such initiative may require the U.S. Postal Service to obtain a signature from that person in order to deliver the document.</p>]]></text>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2016-04-19T20:45:22Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <updateDate>2016-03-03T05:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
        </item>
        <item>
          <actionDate>2016-09-21</actionDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Strengthening the Department of Homeland Security Secure Mail Initiative Act</strong></p> <p>(Sec. 2) This bill requires the Department of Homeland Security to provide an option under the Secure Mail Initiative under which, for payment of a fee recouping costs, a person to whom a document is sent under such initiative may require the U.S. Postal Service to obtain a signature from that person in order to deliver the document. </p>]]></text>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2016-11-18T20:16:40Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <updateDate>2016-09-21T13:51:33Z</updateDate>
          <actionDesc>Passed House amended</actionDesc>
